  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Not Accepted — discretization shortfall)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed, 6 factors scoped-out or not-applicable. The discretization error factor achieved only Gradation 1 against a required Gradation 2, constituting a documented credibility shortfall. The assessment team determined that the shortfall cannot be offset and the package is therefore Not Accepted pending remediation of the mesh convergence study.",
