        "name": "Discretization error Gradation 2 — GCI < 5% on QoI with three systematically refined meshes",
        "description": "Three systematically refined meshes (refinement ratio r = 1.3) must be run and the Grid Convergence Index (GCI) on the relative hemolysis index QoI must be less than 5% at the worst-case operating point. Richardson extrapolation must confirm monotonic convergence."
      },
      "rationale": "Only two mesh levels were completed prior to the submission deadline. The GCI computed from the two available meshes (coarse: 2.1M cells; medium: 3.6M cells) is 11.3% on peak RH, exceeding the 5% acceptance criterion. A third fine mesh (target 6.2M cells) is in preparation but results are not yet available. The factor achieves only Gradation 1 (single mesh, no systematic convergence study) and does not meet the required Gradation 2. This shortfall is the primary basis for the Not Accepted decision."
