        "name": "Validation relevance Gradation 2 — validation scenario matches COU geometry and flow regime",
        "description": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry (FDA GCBP) and overlapping flow rate and speed ranges as the COU operating envelope."
      },
      "rationale": "Validation experiments were conducted on the identical FDA GCBP geometry at flow rates of 2–6 L/min and speeds of 2500–3500 RPM, fully overlapping the COU operating envelope. The validation scenario is therefore directly relevant to the COU without extrapolation."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nse-cou1",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error (iterative convergence and round-off) is scoped out at MRL 2 for this COU because the commercially validated solver (ANSYS Fluent 2023 R2) enforces residual convergence to 1e-6 on all equations and double-precision arithmetic is used throughout. Solver error is demonstrably dominated by discretization error, which is assessed separately. Scoping is consistent with ASME V&V 40 Table 3 guidance for MRL 2 with a validated commercial code."
    },
    {
