      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Model input uncertainty (blood viscosity, inlet velocity profile) is scoped out at MRL 2. A one-at-a-time sensitivity study showed that ±10% variation in blood analog viscosity produces ±3.1% change in RH, and ±5% variation in inlet flow rate produces ±4.8% change in RH. These sensitivities are within the experimental uncertainty band and do not materially affect the worst-case operating point ranking."
    },
